radiographic_examinations.findings: Focus of bifrosis in the right lower lobe, calcified 2 mm nodule in the left lower lobe compatible with a granuloma, small focus of consolidation seen in the lingula, 9-mm stone in the gallbladder neck, mild gallbladder wall thickening, multiple bilateral low-attenuation renal cortical lesions, 4-mm calculus in the left interpolar region, para pelvic cysts noted, moderate calcification lining the aorta and its visceral branches, and a normal caliber common duct in the pancreatic head.
